built-in object

  • BlsKey- elliptic curve cryptographic algorithm object
  • Buffer- Binary data cache object, used for data processing of io read and write
  • BufferedStream- Cache read objects
  • Chain- Message processor chain processing object
  • ChildProcess- child process object
  • Cipher- Symmetric encryption algorithm object
  • Condition- the condition variable object
  • DbConnection- DBConnection is the base class of database connection, used to establish and maintain a database connection session. It implements the basic operations of connections and serves as the basis for derived classes. At the same time, it supports operations such as starting a transaction, committing a transaction, and rolling back a transaction.
  • DgramSocket- The dgram.Socket object is an EventEmitter that encapsulates the packet function.
  • Digest- Information summary object
  • ECKey- The ECKey class is implemented in the crypto module, which can be used to generate ECDSA key pairs, sign and verify messages, etc.
  • Ed25519Key- elliptic curve cryptographic algorithm object
  • Event- The Event module provides an event object for collaborative shared data operations. It allows synchronous operations between multiple fibers (coroutines) for cooperative multitasking. The event object has three methods: wait, pulse and clear. The wait method will block the current fiber until the event is triggered, the pulse method will wake up all the fibers waiting for the event, and the clear method will reset the event flag to false. By using the coroutine.Event module, developers can control the execution sequence and data sharing between fibers to implement complex business logic.
  • EventEmitter- EventEmitter is an event-triggering object, which can be used to establish an observer pattern, and objects that support event-triggering are inherited from this
  • FSWatcher- File system watch object
  • Fiber- Fiber operation object, this object cannot be created directly
  • File- File operation object, used for reading and writing binary files
  • Handler- Message handler interface
  • HeapGraphEdge- HeapGraphEdge represents the association between two HeapGraphNode nodes, from the upstream node to the downstream node
  • HeapGraphNode- HeapGraphNode represents a node in the heap view
  • HeapSnapshot- HeapSnapshots records the state of the JS heap at a certain moment
  • HttpClient- HttpClient is a class library designed for HTTP client functions, providing basic HTTP/HTTPS requests, proxy access, cookie management and other functions
  • HttpCollection- HttpCollection is a generic container for processing headers, query, form, cookie data in http messages
  • HttpCookie- HttpCookie is a cookie object encapsulated by the HTTP protocol. It provides various attributes for obtaining and setting cookies, and also supports the organization and processing of multiple cookies. It is an important attribute supported by both http.Request and http.Response objects
  • HttpHandler- http protocol conversion processor
  • HttpMessage- http base message object
  • HttpRepeater- HttpRepeater is an HTTP request repeater, which can forward HTTP requests to the specified backend server and get the response. It is often used in complex systems that need to interact with multiple servers on the front end, or for load balancing
  • HttpRequest- HttpRequest is a class used to handle HTTP requests, which allows you to create HTTP requests and interact with the server. You can use it to send GET, POST and other types of HTTP requests to the web server
  • HttpResponse- HttpResponse is an HTTP response object, use the HttpRequest.response object to complete the Http server data response, or http.request request to return the server's response data
  • HttpServer- HttpServer is one of the built-in objects, which is the object used to create HTTP servers. An HttpServer object contains two required parameters: port and event processing interface object. In the event processing interface object, the specific implementation method can be a simple callback function, or use complex routes, chained processing arrays, etc.
  • HttpUploadData- Contains one entry data of multipart
  • HttpsServer- HttpsServer is an object used to create an https server, and the HttpsServer object can use all interface functions and properties of HttpServer. The HttpsServer object can provide ssl encryption protection services for the client by passing in the certificate object (X509Cert type) and key object (PKey type) generated by openssl before creation
  • Image- Image processing objects, used to convert, draw, store and other operations on images
  • Iterator- Iterator object for traversing collection data
  • LevelDB- evelDB is a built-in database operation object of fibjs, which is used to create and manage dictionary objects in the form of key-value pairs. Using the LevelDB object, operations such as key-value pair data storage, query, deletion, and enumeration can be easily implemented. It is based on Google's open source LevelDB implementation, which has the advantages of high efficiency, reliability, and scalability
  • Lock- Lock is a built-in object that can be used to control the concurrent access of fibers, and can be acquired by one fiber to prevent other fibers from acquiring it at the same time. Lock can be created by coroutine.Lock() function
  • LruCache- LruCache(Least Recently Used Cache) is a class used to maintain the LRU cache. It can store a certain number of values ​​and maintains the size of the container. When new data comes in, if the container has not reached the size limit, the new data can be directly added to the container. If the container is full, the container will evict the least recently used data
  • MemoryStream- memory stream object
  • Message- Basic message object
  • MongoCollection- mongodb database dataset object
  • MongoCursor- mongodb database data cursor object
  • MongoDB- mongodb database connection object
  • MongoID- The mongodb database data uniquely identifies the object, which is used to store and pass the oid
  • MySQL- MySQL objects are classes for manipulating MySQL databases,
  • Odbc- Odbc database connection object
  • PKey- PKey is an object provided by the built-in crypto module that represents a pair of keys: a public key and a private key. PKey supports generating keys, loading keys, storing keys and managing the encryption process in JS
  • RangeStream- Range query stream read object
  • Redis- Redis database client object
  • RedisHash- Redis database client Hash object, this object is the client that contains the specified key, and the database will be operated only when its method is called
  • RedisList- Redis database client List object, this object is the client that contains the specified key, and the database will be operated only when its method is called
  • RedisSet- Redis database client Set object, this object is the client that contains the specified key, and the database will be operated only when its method is called
  • RedisSortedSet- Redis database client SortedSet object, this object is the client that contains the specified key, only when its method is called will the database be operated
  • Routing- message handler route object
  • SQLite- The SQLite object is a member of the built-in module db, which is mainly responsible for the connection and operation of the SQLite database, and can be used for operations such as creation, query, insertion, and update of the SQLite database. At the same time, the SQLite object also provides some advanced operations such as backup and formatting SQL. SQLite connection objects also support transactional operations
  • SandBox- Security sandbox object, used to manage an independent running space
  • SeekableStream- A stream object interface that can move the current pointer
  • Semaphore- fiber semaphore object
  • Service- System service management object
  • Smtp- Smtp object
  • Socket- Network socket object
  • SslHandler- ssl protocol conversion processor
  • SslServer- ssl server object, it is convenient to create a standard multi-fiber ssl server
  • SslSocket- ssl network socket object
  • Stat- The basic information object of the file
  • StatsWatcher- File Stats observation object
  • Stream- Stream operation object, used for binary data stream reading and writing
  • StringDecoder- stream decoding object
  • TTYInputStream- tty read stream object, used to read and write to tty
  • TTYOutputStream- tty write stream object, used to handle tty output
  • TcpServer- TcpServer` is a high-concurrency TCP Socket server, which can be used to create a TCP server that has established a TCP connection with the client in the initial state
  • TextDecoder- TextDecoder decoding object
  • TextEncoder- TextEncoder encoding object
  • Timer- Timer handler object
  • UrlObject- UrlObject is an object used to represent URL information, we can conveniently use UrlObject object to represent and operate a URL address.
  • WebSocket- WebSocket is a full-duplex communication protocol based on the TCP protocol. It establishes an uninterrupted connection between the browser and the server, can realize real-time two-way data transmission, and can support data transmission in any format. In fibjs, the WebSocket support module provides the corresponding API interface, which can realize the development of WebSocket server and client
  • WebSocketMessage- WebSocketMessageis a message type in the WebSocket protocol, which encapsulates the data format and processing methods of various messages in the WebSocket transport protocol, and can be used for communication between the WebSocket client and server.
  • WebView- browser window object
  • Worker- The Worker object is an object used to create sub-threads, which can be created and processed in the program. A Worker object can be understood as a JavaScript process that executes in a thread different from the main thread. Worker does not share memory with the main thread and will not block the main thread. It is a mainstream asynchronous programming method
  • X509Cert- X509Cert is the object representing the x509 certificate in the crypto module. This object mainly includes certificate information and methods constructed from a certificate data in DER or PEM format and certificate chain data, and can perform operations such as certificate parsing and verification.
  • X509Crl- The X509Crl object is an object in the crypto module, which is used to represent the X509 revoked certificate, that is, the revocation list of the certificate. CA-related operations such as the verification of the X509 certificate chain will use the revocation list information
  • X509Req- The X509Req object is an object used to create an x509 certificate request and belongs to the crypto module
  • XmlAttr- An XmlAttr object representing an attribute of an XmlElement object
  • XmlCDATASection- An XmlCDATASection object representing a CDATA section in a document
  • XmlCharacterData- XmlCharacterData interface provides common functions of XmlText and XmlComment nodes
  • XmlComment- An XmlComment object representing the content of a comment node in the document
  • XmlDocument- XmlDocument is an object of the xml module, which represents the entire XML document and provides access to the entire document
  • XmlDocumentType- The XmlDocumentType object is used to access entities defined by XML
  • XmlElement- An XmlElement object representing an element in an XML document
  • XmlNamedNodeMap- The XmlNamedNodeMap object represents an unordered list of attributes
  • XmlNode- The XmlNode object is the basic data type of the entire DOM
  • XmlNodeList- The XmlNodeList object represents an ordered list of nodes
  • XmlProcessingInstruction- The XmlProcessingInstruction object represents the xml processing instruction
  • XmlText- An XmlText object representing the text content of an element or attribute
  • ZipFile- The ZipFile object is an important object in the zip format file compression and decompression module, which provides read and write access to the zip file
  • object- the base object from which all objects inherit
